paragraphs.title: Clean missing values
paragraphs.text:
%pyspark
print("Missing values before cleaning:")
mlDF.agg(*((n_rows - F.count(c)).alias(c) for c in mlDF.columns)).show()

def fix_missing_age(df):
    mean_age = df.select('Age').groupBy().mean().collect()[0][0]
    return df.fillna({'Age': int(mean_age)})

def fix_missing_embarked(df):
    mode = df.select('Embarked').groupBy().count().first()[0]
    return df.fillna({"Embarked":mode})

print("Cleaning Age")
mlDF = fix_missing_age(mlDF)
print("Cleaning Embarked")
mlDF = fix_missing_embarked(mlDF)
print("Cleaning Fare")
mlDF = mlDF.fillna({"Fare":0.0})
print("Transforming Cabin")
mlDF = mlDF.withColumn('Has_Cabin',F.col('Cabin').isNotNull().cast('int'))
mlDF = mlDF.drop(F.col('Cabin'))

print("Missing values after cleaning:")
mlDF.agg(*((n_rows - F.count(c)).alias(c) for c in mlDF.columns)).show()

paragraphs.title: Feature engineering
paragraphs.text:
%pyspark
# Extract the titles from names
mlDF = mlDF.___('Title', F.regexp_extract(F.___('Name'), ' ([A-Za-z]+)\.', 1))

title_class = {
    'Capt': 'Rare',
    'Col':'Rare',
    'Don': 'Rare',
    'Dr': 'Rare',
    'Major': 'Rare',
    'Rev': 'Rare',
    'Jonkheer': 'Rare',
    'Dona': 'Rare',
    'Countess': 'Royal',
    'Lady': 'Royal',
    'Sir': 'Royal',
    'Mlle': 'Miss',
    'Ms': 'Miss',
    'Mme': 'Mrs'
}

# Aggregate titles by replacing them
mlDF = mlDF.replace(title_class, None, 'Title')

# Drop the old Name column
mlDF = mlDF.drop(F.col('Name'))

paragraphs.title: Prepare data for ML
paragraphs.text:
%pyspark
def string_to_index(df, column):
    indexer = StringIndexer(inputCol=column, outputCol="{}Index".format(column))
    df = indexer.fit(df).transform(df)
    return df

mlDF = string_to_index(mlDF, "Sex")
mlDF = string_to_index(mlDF, "Title")
mlDF = string_to_index(mlDF, "Embarked")

mlDF = mlDF.withColumn('Age2', F.col('Age').cast('int'))
mlDF = mlDF.drop('Age')
mlDF = mlDF.withColumnRenamed('Age2', 'Age')

cols = ['Pclass', 'Age', 'SibSp', 'Parch', 'Fare', 'Has_Cabin', 'SexIndex', 'TitleIndex', 'EmbarkedIndex']

assembler = VectorAssembler(
  inputCols = cols, outputCol="features"
)

ml_data = assembler.transform(mlDF).select('features', F.col('label').cast('int'))

paragraphs.title: Split data into test and train set
paragraphs.text:
%pyspark
train, test = ml_data.randomSplit([0.7, 0.3], seed = 0)
print("We have %d rows of training data and %d rows of testing data." % (train.count(), test.count()))

paragraphs.title: Define the evaluation methods
paragraphs.text:
%pyspark
evaluator = BinaryClassificationEvaluator(metricName='areaUnderROC')

    
def evaluate_model(predictions):
    evaluator = BinaryClassificationEvaluator()
    evaluator.evaluate(predictions)
    print("{} is: {}".format(evaluator.getMetricName(), evaluator.evaluate(predictions)))
    evaluator.setMetricName("areaUnderPR")
    evaluator.evaluate(predictions)
    print("{} is: {}".format(evaluator.getMetricName(), evaluator.evaluate(predictions)))
    
    predictionAndLabels = predictions.select('prediction', F.col('label').cast('double')).rdd
    metrics = MulticlassMetrics(predictionAndLabels)
    
    print("Weighted recall is: {}".format(metrics.weightedRecall))
    print("Weighted precision is: {}".format(metrics.weightedPrecision))
    print("Weighted F(1) Score is {}".format(metrics.weightedFMeasure()))
    print("Weighted F(0.5) Score is {}".format(metrics.weightedFMeasure(beta=0.5)))
    print("Weighted false positive rate is: {}".format(metrics.weightedFalsePositiveRate))

msg.data:
Explore Random Forest

Documentation: https://spark.apache.org/docs/2.4.4/api/python/pyspark.ml.html#pyspark.ml.classification.RandomForestClassifier

First we will train and evaluate a Random Forest, after that we’ll perform parameter tuning on a few of the parameters and evaluate the best model.

paragraphs.text:
%pyspark
rf = RandomForestClassifier(featuresCol="features", labelCol="label", numTrees=50, maxDepth=30, seed=42)
model = rf.fit(train)

predictions = model.transform(test)
evaluate_model(predictions=predictions)

paragraphs.title: Random Forest GridSearch
paragraphs.text:
%pyspark
paramGrid = (ParamGridBuilder()
             .addGrid(rf.maxDepth, [3,15])
             .addGrid(rf.maxBins, [20, 60])
             .addGrid(rf.numTrees, [5, 50])
             .addGrid(rf.impurity, ["gini"])
             .addGrid(rf.featureSubsetStrategy, ['auto', 'sqrt'])
             .build())

cv = CrossValidator(estimator=rf, estimatorParamMaps=paramGrid, evaluator=evaluator, numFolds=2)

cvModel = cv.fit(train)

print("Best model has the following params:\n maxDepth: {}\n maxBins: {}\n numTrees: {}\n Impuruty: {}\n FeauteSubset: {}".format(
    cvModel.bestModel._java_obj.getMaxDepth(), 
    cvModel.bestModel._java_obj.getMaxBins(), 
    cvModel.bestModel._java_obj.getNumTrees(),
    cvModel.bestModel._java_obj.getImpurity(),
    cvModel.bestModel._java_obj.getFeatureSubsetStrategy()
    ))

predictions = cvModel.bestModel.transform(test)
evaluate_model(predictions=predictions)

paragraphs.title: Explore Decission Trees
paragraphs.text:
%pyspark
dt = DecisionTreeClassifier(labelCol="label", featuresCol="features", maxDepth=3, impurity='Entropy')
dtModel = dt.fit(train)

predictions = dtModel.transform(test)
evaluate_model(predictions=predictions)

%pyspark
paramGrid = (ParamGridBuilder()
             .addGrid(dt.maxDepth, [1, 2, 6, 10])
             .addGrid(dt.maxBins, [20, 40, 80])
             .build())

cv = CrossValidator(estimator=dt, estimatorParamMaps=paramGrid, evaluator=BinaryClassificationEvaluator(), numFolds=5)
cvModel = cv.fit(train)

print("Best numNodes: {}".format(cvModel.bestModel.numNodes))
print("Best depth: {}".format(cvModel.bestModel.depth))

predictions = cvModel.bestModel.transform(test)
evaluate_model(predictions=predictions)
